00:34:15.850 --> 00:34:21.090
And at the same time, it's important that we make note of something

00:34:21.090 --> 00:34:23.610
that had happened in the battle of that Al-Riqa'a.

00:34:23.610 --> 00:34:27.250
There is difference of opinion as to when exactly that Al-Riqa'a took place.

00:34:27.250 --> 00:34:33.010
It was a battle where when the Muslims' time for prayer had come,

00:34:33.010 --> 00:34:36.290
the non-Muslims had thought when these people go to sajda,

00:34:36.290 --> 00:34:38.450
we can wipe them out because they have to pray.

00:34:38.450 --> 00:34:41.170
And when they are praying, they all go down in prostration.

00:34:41.170 --> 00:34:44.090
When they are prostrating, it will be easy to wipe them out.

00:34:44.090 --> 00:34:48.570
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala revealed to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:34:48.570 --> 00:34:57.210
وَإِذَا ضَرَبْتُمْ فِي الْأَرْضِ فَلَيْسَ عَلَيْكُمْ جُنَاحٌ أَنْ تَقْصُرُوا مِنَ الصَّلَاةِ إِنْ خِفْتُمْ

00:34:57.210 --> 00:35:02.210
إِنْ خِفْتُمْ أَنْ يَفْتِنَكُمُ الَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا

00:35:02.210 --> 00:35:05.930
When you are traveling on land and you are fearful,

00:35:05.930 --> 00:35:09.970
you are scared, meaning there is fear of the enemy attacking you.

00:35:09.970 --> 00:35:12.890
There is no harm in changing the salah.

00:35:12.890 --> 00:35:18.810
When we say changing the salah, meaning the physical postures and movements of salah for that moment,

00:35:18.810 --> 00:35:20.570
there will be a difference in it.

00:35:20.570 --> 00:35:21.530
In what way?

00:35:21.530 --> 00:35:23.450
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:35:23.450 --> 00:35:32.610
وَإِذَا كُنتَ فِيهِمْ فَأَقَمْتَ لَهُمُ الصَّلَاةَ فَالْتَقُمْ طَائِفَةٌ مِنْهُمْ مَعَكُ

00:35:32.610 --> 00:35:36.690
Long verses that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala makes mention of in Surah An-Nisa.

00:35:36.690 --> 00:35:39.410
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:35:39.450 --> 00:35:43.090
there should be a group of people when they go down to sajda,

00:35:43.090 --> 00:35:46.450
there must be another group of people who have not gone down to sajda

00:35:46.450 --> 00:35:48.010
and they are waiting with their weapons.

00:35:48.010 --> 00:35:48.890
Allahu akbar.

00:35:48.890 --> 00:35:50.930
When these have completed with their sajda,

00:35:50.930 --> 00:35:53.090
these people will then go down to their sajda

00:35:53.090 --> 00:35:54.770
and those will be waiting with their weapons.

00:35:54.770 --> 00:35:56.130
So they will take turns.

00:35:56.130 --> 00:35:57.010
Allahu akbar.

00:35:57.010 --> 00:35:58.330
Look at the salah.

00:35:58.330 --> 00:36:00.410
And when they had done this,

00:36:00.410 --> 00:36:03.250
the mushriks were shocked because their plan.

00:36:03.250 --> 00:36:05.010
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:36:09.410 --> 00:36:14.090
The disbelievers had hoped that whilst you are oblivious of your items

00:36:14.090 --> 00:36:17.410
and your armor and your belongings,

00:36:17.410 --> 00:36:20.250
they could have wiped you out at once.

00:36:20.250 --> 00:36:21.810
And Allah says,

00:36:21.810 --> 00:36:24.130
you change, you can change the method

00:36:24.130 --> 00:36:28.330
or the physical method of salah for that particular time

00:36:28.330 --> 00:36:30.850
where one group goes down, the other one is waiting.

00:36:30.850 --> 00:36:32.610
When that one comes up, this one goes down,

00:36:32.610 --> 00:36:33.890
whilst that one goes down,

00:36:33.890 --> 00:36:35.130
the other group goes down,

00:36:35.130 --> 00:36:36.330
the other group goes down,

00:36:36.330 --> 00:36:37.530
the other group goes down,

00:36:37.570 --> 00:36:39.130
the other one comes up, this one goes down,

00:36:39.130 --> 00:36:40.250
whilst that one is waiting.

00:36:40.250 --> 00:36:41.050
Subhanallah.

00:36:41.050 --> 00:36:42.530
Then they join together.

00:36:42.530 --> 00:36:44.730
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:36:44.730 --> 00:36:46.490
This had also come down.

00:36:46.490 --> 00:36:50.250
Another very interesting point I want to make mention of

00:36:50.250 --> 00:36:54.130
is that Zayd ibn Thabit radiallahu anhu,

00:36:54.130 --> 00:36:55.850
the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam told him,

00:36:55.850 --> 00:36:57.890
O Zayd, I need you,

00:36:57.890 --> 00:37:00.450
I need you to learn the language,

00:37:00.450 --> 00:37:03.530
the Hebrew language because we don't trust these people

00:37:03.530 --> 00:37:05.450
and we would like to know this language.

00:37:05.450 --> 00:37:07.410
Zayd ibn Thabit radiallahu anhu

00:37:07.410 --> 00:37:10.490
started learning Hebrew within 15 days.

00:37:10.490 --> 00:37:12.970
He learned the Hebrew language completely

00:37:12.970 --> 00:37:14.530
and he was a master at it.

00:37:14.530 --> 00:37:17.050
Later on, when the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:37:17.050 --> 00:37:18.690
wrote letters to some of the kings,

00:37:18.690 --> 00:37:21.930
he had told him to learn a different language

00:37:21.930 --> 00:37:24.170
known as Assyriania

00:37:24.170 --> 00:37:27.130
and he learned it again in less than a month.

00:37:27.130 --> 00:37:28.490
I have a question.

00:37:28.490 --> 00:37:30.330
We all say, I want to learn Arabic.

00:37:30.330 --> 00:37:31.970
Anytime you see someone, they say,

00:37:31.970 --> 00:37:33.290
I want to learn Arabic.

00:37:33.290 --> 00:37:34.450
I want to learn Arabic.

00:37:34.450 --> 00:37:36.690
Forget about 15 days.

00:37:36.690 --> 00:37:38.690
15 years have gone by,

00:37:38.690 --> 00:37:40.330
we still don't know the language.

00:37:40.330 --> 00:37:41.730
Look at the dedication of those

00:37:41.730 --> 00:37:43.130
and where's our dedication?

00:37:43.130 --> 00:37:45.250
May Allah open us and open our doors.

00:37:45.250 --> 00:37:47.050
May He make it easy for us.

00:37:47.050 --> 00:37:50.170
At least if not 15 days, then 15 months

00:37:50.170 --> 00:37:51.850
and if not 15 months, come on,

00:37:51.850 --> 00:37:53.810
15 years can go by,

00:37:53.810 --> 00:37:55.250
but would you know something?

00:37:55.250 --> 00:37:58.010
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us dedication.

00:37:58.010 --> 00:38:00.490
I think if we all learn a few words a day

00:38:00.490 --> 00:38:02.610
of the Arabic language, believe me,

00:38:02.610 --> 00:38:04.050
within a short space of time,

00:38:04.050 --> 00:38:05.490
we would know a lot.

00:38:05.490 --> 00:38:08.570
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:38:08.570 --> 00:38:10.130
Then there is an incident in history

00:38:10.130 --> 00:38:14.110
that we are going to make mention of today.

00:38:14.110 --> 00:38:16.550
There was a man known as Zayd ibn Harithah.

00:38:16.550 --> 00:38:17.950
Not the same Zayd ibn Thabit

00:38:17.950 --> 00:38:20.070
we spoke about languages about, no.

00:38:20.070 --> 00:38:22.910
Another man known as Zayd ibn Harithah.

00:38:22.910 --> 00:38:26.910
If you remember, he was the slave boy

00:38:26.910 --> 00:38:28.990
who was freed by Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:38:28.990 --> 00:38:32.510
and he accepted Islam right at the beginning

00:38:32.510 --> 00:38:35.270
and he refused to go back with his parents.

00:38:35.270 --> 00:38:37.190
He was so close to the messenger.

00:38:37.190 --> 00:38:38.950
The messenger sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:38:38.950 --> 00:38:42.030
had adopted him and he was known as Zayd ibn Muhammad.

00:38:42.030 --> 00:38:43.110
Zayd, the son of Muhammad.

00:38:43.110 --> 00:38:45.390
Everyone knew him as Zayd ibn Muhammad.

00:38:45.390 --> 00:38:47.310
Zayd, the son of Muhammad.

00:38:47.310 --> 00:38:50.790
So this was something that the people at that time

00:38:50.790 --> 00:38:55.270
were indulged in, engrossed in,

00:38:55.270 --> 00:38:57.710
very deeply believing in.

00:38:57.710 --> 00:38:58.870
What was this belief?

00:38:58.870 --> 00:39:01.230
You adopt someone, you change their name

00:39:01.230 --> 00:39:03.950
to your own name and you begin to say,

00:39:03.990 --> 00:39:06.870
this person is son of so and so, yet they are not.

00:39:06.870 --> 00:39:08.590
But just because you've adopted them,

00:39:08.590 --> 00:39:10.150
you've changed their name.

00:39:10.150 --> 00:39:13.670
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala wanted this

00:39:13.670 --> 00:39:15.830
to be crushed forever.

00:39:15.830 --> 00:39:18.790
It was a belief where, remember,

00:39:18.790 --> 00:39:21.750
Nasab and your lineage is sacred.

00:39:21.750 --> 00:39:25.350
Allah created you and He chose for you your parents,

00:39:25.350 --> 00:39:27.870
whether they are good or bad is besides the point.

00:39:27.870 --> 00:39:30.350
You have to be linked to your father,

00:39:30.350 --> 00:39:32.390
whether you like him or you don't like him.

00:39:32.390 --> 00:39:35.710
You will be called not by your mother's name

00:39:35.710 --> 00:39:36.750
on the day of Qiyamah.

00:39:36.750 --> 00:39:39.350
No, no, not at all.

00:39:39.350 --> 00:39:40.910
Those who think you are going to be called

00:39:40.910 --> 00:39:43.510
by your mother's name in order to protect people

00:39:43.510 --> 00:39:47.390
from adultery and meaning being exposed on that day,

00:39:47.390 --> 00:39:48.510
that is not true.

00:39:48.510 --> 00:39:51.030
It is completely fabricated, no.

00:39:51.030 --> 00:39:52.790
You will be called your name,

00:39:52.790 --> 00:39:55.150
son of so and so with your father's name.

00:39:55.150 --> 00:39:56.470
The story is over.

00:39:56.470 --> 00:39:59.110
That is authentic and without a dispute.

00:39:59.110 --> 00:40:00.910
So the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam says,

00:40:00.910 --> 00:40:02.310
give your children good names

00:40:02.310 --> 00:40:03.990
because they will be called by their names

00:40:03.990 --> 00:40:07.390
and their father's names on the day of Qiyamah.

00:40:07.390 --> 00:40:10.310
Now, at that time, they were saying Zaydi bin Muhammad.

00:40:10.310 --> 00:40:12.550
The Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam had adopted him.

00:40:12.550 --> 00:40:14.990
Then Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala had,

00:40:14.990 --> 00:40:18.910
with his divine wisdom, obviously planned something.

00:40:18.910 --> 00:40:21.270
There was a cousin of the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:40:21.270 --> 00:40:23.310
by the name of Zainab binti Jahsh.

00:40:23.310 --> 00:40:25.990
Her mother was the aunt of Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:40:25.990 --> 00:40:29.710
Umaymah binti Abd al-Muttalib.

00:40:29.710 --> 00:40:32.670
And she was the aunt of Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:40:32.670 --> 00:40:34.510
and this was the cousin.

00:40:34.510 --> 00:40:37.110
He told her, oh Zainab,

00:40:37.110 --> 00:40:39.110
I would like you to marry Zayd,

00:40:39.110 --> 00:40:40.670
Zayd meaning Zayd ibn Muhammad,

00:40:40.670 --> 00:40:44.870
this man Zayd ibn Harith who was known at that time as that.

00:40:44.870 --> 00:40:47.230
So she said, no man, I don't want to marry him.

00:40:47.230 --> 00:40:51.670
He is formerly a slave and he is like this and like that and so on.

00:40:51.670 --> 00:40:57.870
And this Zayd was married to someone known as Umayman.

00:40:57.910 --> 00:41:01.870
And she had had his child known as Usama ibn Zayd.

00:41:01.870 --> 00:41:05.110
Umayman was a woman from Africa, as we had told you.

00:41:05.110 --> 00:41:07.190
She looked after Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:41:07.190 --> 00:41:10.470
from the point of birth right up to adulthood,

00:41:10.470 --> 00:41:12.310
Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:41:12.310 --> 00:41:13.550
That was Umayman.

00:41:13.550 --> 00:41:14.750
And the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:41:14.750 --> 00:41:15.590
made an announcement,

00:41:15.590 --> 00:41:17.830
whoever wants to marry a woman from paradise,

00:41:17.830 --> 00:41:21.270
marry this woman and Zayd ibn Harith married her.

00:41:21.270 --> 00:41:23.630
This was Umayman, radiallahu anha.

00:41:23.630 --> 00:41:26.350
Now Zainab binti Jahsh is saying,

00:41:26.350 --> 00:41:28.630
I don't want to marry him.

00:41:28.630 --> 00:41:30.790
But the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam said,

00:41:30.790 --> 00:41:32.950
this is an instruction.

00:41:32.950 --> 00:41:34.070
Verses were revealed.

00:41:34.070 --> 00:41:35.110
Listen to the verses.

00:41:35.110 --> 00:41:37.790
We need them today, desperately.

00:41:37.790 --> 00:41:41.150
Wama kaana limu'minun wala mu'minatin

00:41:41.150 --> 00:41:44.950
idaa qad allahu wa rasuluhu

00:41:44.950 --> 00:41:50.030
amran ayyakoon lahumul khiyaratu min amrihim.

00:41:50.030 --> 00:41:54.070
It is not for a believing male or a believing female

00:41:54.070 --> 00:41:57.310
that when Allah and His Rasul have decided something

00:41:57.310 --> 00:41:59.430
and commanded and instructed something

00:41:59.430 --> 00:42:02.830
that they think they have a choice in that regard.

00:42:02.830 --> 00:42:04.470
A believing male and women,

00:42:04.470 --> 00:42:06.190
a believing male and female,

00:42:06.190 --> 00:42:09.030
when Allah and His messenger have instructed something,

00:42:09.030 --> 00:42:11.950
they know they have no choice in that regard.

00:42:11.950 --> 00:42:13.590
They must get it done.

00:42:13.590 --> 00:42:14.750
That's a sign of belief.

00:42:14.750 --> 00:42:16.590
May Allah grant it to us.

00:42:16.590 --> 00:42:17.790
Today someone says, you know brother,

00:42:17.790 --> 00:42:18.710
interest is haram.

00:42:18.710 --> 00:42:21.350
Say, no man, I heard that if you do it this way,

00:42:21.350 --> 00:42:22.710
that way, then it's okay.

00:42:22.710 --> 00:42:23.790
Interest is haram.

00:42:23.790 --> 00:42:25.430
Close the door and carry on.

00:42:25.430 --> 00:42:27.070
Someone says, you know adultery is haram.

00:42:27.070 --> 00:42:28.470
No, but those people,

00:42:28.470 --> 00:42:30.510
they can do something temporary, you know.

00:42:30.510 --> 00:42:31.350
Astaghfirullah.

00:42:31.350 --> 00:42:32.750
Why use different names?

00:42:32.750 --> 00:42:34.430
Why say different things?

00:42:34.430 --> 00:42:35.670
Why con yourself?

00:42:35.670 --> 00:42:37.670
Surrender to the law of Allah.

00:42:37.670 --> 00:42:39.750
So the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:42:39.750 --> 00:42:42.150
when he said this, Zainab bint Jah says,

00:42:42.150 --> 00:42:44.310
I hear and I obey.

00:42:44.310 --> 00:42:49.310
And she married this man, Zaid ibn Harithah,

00:42:49.310 --> 00:42:51.590
radiallahu anhu.

00:42:51.590 --> 00:42:54.950
It so happened that he had a difficulty.

00:42:54.950 --> 00:42:56.430
There was no compatibility.

00:42:56.430 --> 00:42:57.870
We believe they were both Sahaba.

00:42:57.870 --> 00:42:59.910
It was Allah's divine plan.

00:42:59.910 --> 00:43:01.230
There was no compatibility.

00:43:01.230 --> 00:43:03.550
Zainab bint Jah did not get along

00:43:03.550 --> 00:43:05.350
with Zaid ibn Harithah

00:43:05.350 --> 00:43:07.590
and he did not get along with her.

00:43:07.590 --> 00:43:09.550
We don't know of the details of what happened,

00:43:09.550 --> 00:43:12.910
but the most respectful term for us to say is,

00:43:12.910 --> 00:43:14.190
there was no compatibility.

00:43:14.190 --> 00:43:15.270
Two brilliant people,

00:43:15.270 --> 00:43:17.270
but brought up slightly differently.

00:43:17.270 --> 00:43:19.350
And therefore you find difference.

00:43:19.350 --> 00:43:21.070
And he used to come complaining

00:43:21.070 --> 00:43:22.230
to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:43:22.230 --> 00:43:24.430
and Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam used to tell him,

00:43:24.430 --> 00:43:26.790
fear Allah and hold her.

00:43:26.790 --> 00:43:29.590
Ittaqillah, fear Allah and hold her.

00:43:29.590 --> 00:43:31.430
And Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala

00:43:31.430 --> 00:43:34.630
then sent revelation to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:43:34.630 --> 00:43:36.870
telling him, informing him

00:43:36.870 --> 00:43:40.670
that he will be married off to Zainab bint Jah

00:43:40.670 --> 00:43:44.230
after Zaid divorces Zainab.

00:43:44.230 --> 00:43:46.070
And the reason for this is,

00:43:46.070 --> 00:43:49.590
so that people know that Zaid is not your son.

00:43:49.590 --> 00:43:52.870
And so that the laws of adoption

00:43:52.870 --> 00:43:55.310
be made clear in Islam

00:43:55.310 --> 00:43:58.030
and distinguished from the laws of adoption

00:43:58.030 --> 00:44:01.070
that had reigned at the time of the pagan Arabs

00:44:01.070 --> 00:44:01.950
for that reason.

00:44:01.950 --> 00:44:03.110
It was very clear.

00:44:04.070 --> 00:44:06.150
So Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala

00:44:06.150 --> 00:44:10.110
then speaks about Zaid radiallahu anhu

00:44:10.110 --> 00:44:14.590
and how Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala

00:44:14.590 --> 00:44:17.030
got Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:44:17.030 --> 00:44:18.830
married from the heavens.

00:44:18.830 --> 00:44:20.790
The marriage was done from the heavens.

00:44:20.790 --> 00:44:23.950
He went in, the mahr was 400 dirhams

00:44:23.950 --> 00:44:25.670
and he had paid her the mahr

00:44:25.670 --> 00:44:28.030
after Zaid ibn Haritha divorced her.

00:44:28.030 --> 00:44:29.950
And the idda period was over

00:44:29.950 --> 00:44:31.350
and he took her as a wife,

00:44:31.350 --> 00:44:33.470
made an announcement and had a walima

00:44:33.470 --> 00:44:35.150
amongst his companions.

00:44:35.150 --> 00:44:38.990
And the people were very, very amazed

00:44:38.990 --> 00:44:40.430
because they learned something

00:44:40.430 --> 00:44:41.630
through the revelation

00:44:41.630 --> 00:44:44.030
that had come from Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:44:44.150 --> 00:44:47.150
When Zaid radiallahu anhu divorced her,

00:44:47.150 --> 00:44:48.790
we got her married to you,

00:44:48.790 --> 00:44:51.230
O Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:44:51.230 --> 00:44:54.950
Likayla yakoona ala almu'mineena haraj

00:44:54.950 --> 00:44:59.070
fi azwaji ad'iyaihim

00:44:59.070 --> 00:45:02.910
ida qadaw minhunna wa tara

00:45:02.910 --> 00:45:05.230
So that none of you

00:45:05.230 --> 00:45:07.710
could have any form of marriage

00:45:07.710 --> 00:45:10.150
or any other form of marriage.

00:45:10.150 --> 00:45:12.350
So that none of you

00:45:12.670 --> 00:45:15.510
could have any form of doubt

00:45:15.510 --> 00:45:19.150
regarding the marriage of a person

00:45:19.150 --> 00:45:25.110
to the ex-wife of his so-called adopted son,

00:45:25.110 --> 00:45:26.550
which means this is not your son.

00:45:26.550 --> 00:45:27.910
If he was your real son,

00:45:27.910 --> 00:45:30.230
you would never be allowed to marry her

00:45:30.230 --> 00:45:32.230
because that was your daughter-in-law

00:45:32.230 --> 00:45:33.390
prohibited upon you

00:45:33.390 --> 00:45:36.390
even after she is divorced.

00:45:36.390 --> 00:45:38.550
So this was Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:45:38.550 --> 00:45:39.790
And in the same surah

00:45:39.790 --> 00:45:41.230
known as Suratul Ahzab,

00:45:41.270 --> 00:45:43.790
remember this all happened after Al Ahzab.

00:45:43.790 --> 00:45:44.750
Right at the beginning,

00:45:44.750 --> 00:45:46.350
Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala says,

00:45:46.350 --> 00:45:48.670
if you open the pages of Suratul Ahzab,

00:45:48.670 --> 00:45:51.110
very interesting, powerful surah.

00:45:51.110 --> 00:45:53.110
Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala says,

00:45:53.110 --> 00:45:58.190
wa ma ja'ala ad'iyaaakum abnaaakum

00:45:58.190 --> 00:46:00.790
Those whom you are claiming to have adopted,

00:46:00.790 --> 00:46:02.470
we have not made them your sons.

00:46:02.470 --> 00:46:03.630
They are not your sons.

00:46:03.630 --> 00:46:04.430
Allah says,

00:46:04.430 --> 00:46:08.110
ادعوهم لآبائهم

00:46:08.110 --> 00:46:11.310
هو أقسط عند الله

00:46:11.310 --> 00:46:13.590
Call them with their father's names.

00:46:13.590 --> 00:46:17.070
That is justice according to Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:46:17.070 --> 00:46:20.150
And this is why it is totally prohibited

00:46:20.150 --> 00:46:22.990
to lie and say this is so-and-so,

00:46:22.990 --> 00:46:24.350
son of so-and-so,

00:46:24.350 --> 00:46:26.710
knowing that this is not true.

00:46:26.710 --> 00:46:28.470
If you've adopted someone,

00:46:28.470 --> 00:46:29.750
you can always inform them.

00:46:29.750 --> 00:46:31.510
They need to know who they are.

00:46:31.550 --> 00:46:34.470
Lineage is sacred in Islam.

00:46:34.470 --> 00:46:36.390
And this is why the hadith says,

00:46:36.390 --> 00:46:38.670
whoever changes lineage,

00:46:38.670 --> 00:46:42.150
knowing that this is untrue,

00:46:42.150 --> 00:46:44.270
they will not smell the scent of heaven.

00:46:44.270 --> 00:46:45.190
Allahu Akbar.

00:46:45.190 --> 00:46:46.750
They will not smell the scent of heaven

00:46:46.750 --> 00:46:48.390
because it is sacred.

00:46:48.390 --> 00:46:50.830
And whoever calls themselves

00:46:50.830 --> 00:46:53.710
with a name besides that of their father's,

00:46:53.710 --> 00:46:55.710
meaning son of so-and-so.

00:46:55.710 --> 00:46:56.990
You see surnames,

00:46:56.990 --> 00:46:59.990
a surname is something that people create.

00:46:59.990 --> 00:47:01.710
A man sells milk,

00:47:01.710 --> 00:47:04.950
they call him so-and-so milkman.

00:47:04.950 --> 00:47:06.430
You know, a man sells,

00:47:06.430 --> 00:47:07.670
I know in Urdu they would say,

00:47:07.670 --> 00:47:09.550
or in Gujarati they would say Dudwala,

00:47:09.550 --> 00:47:11.510
which means a person who sells milk.

00:47:11.510 --> 00:47:12.910
For example, in another language,

00:47:12.910 --> 00:47:13.910
they might say Najar,

00:47:13.910 --> 00:47:15.550
which means a carpenter.

00:47:15.550 --> 00:47:16.390
They will say,

00:47:16.390 --> 00:47:18.310
so a surname is just something

00:47:18.310 --> 00:47:19.430
that people are known by.

00:47:19.430 --> 00:47:20.550
No harm in surnames.

00:47:20.550 --> 00:47:21.950
We're not worried.

00:47:21.950 --> 00:47:23.990
But at the same time to say

00:47:23.990 --> 00:47:26.270
that this person is the son of so-and-so

00:47:26.270 --> 00:47:29.030
or to give people the feeling

00:47:29.030 --> 00:47:32.110
that this person is actually belonging to someone

00:47:32.110 --> 00:47:33.710
whom he is not belonging to.

00:47:33.710 --> 00:47:35.030
That is what we're talking about.

00:47:35.030 --> 00:47:37.270
Allah says, even if you don't know their parents,

00:47:37.270 --> 00:47:38.190
you should call them,

00:47:38.190 --> 00:47:39.790
these are the sons of Abdullah.

00:47:39.790 --> 00:47:43.030
فَإِلَّمْ تَعْلَمُوا أَبَاءَهُمْ فَإِخْوَانُكُمْ فِي الدِّيلِ

00:47:43.030 --> 00:47:45.710
These are our brothers in Islam.

00:47:45.710 --> 00:47:48.150
This is the verses of Surah Al-Ahzab

00:47:48.150 --> 00:47:51.270
and I invite you to pick up the Quran

00:47:51.270 --> 00:47:54.350
and read the opening verses of Surah Al-Ahzab

00:47:54.350 --> 00:47:56.950
to see what Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has said.

00:47:56.950 --> 00:48:00.110
Because adoption as was known

00:48:00.110 --> 00:48:03.510
at the time of Quraysh was abolished completely.

00:48:03.510 --> 00:48:04.550
So what remained?

00:48:04.550 --> 00:48:08.350
What remained is the virtue of looking after children

00:48:08.350 --> 00:48:09.750
who do not belong to you.

00:48:09.750 --> 00:48:11.150
That's all it was.

00:48:11.150 --> 00:48:13.030
It's just looking after children.

00:48:13.030 --> 00:48:15.470
You have foster children who are not yours.

00:48:15.470 --> 00:48:17.670
We still have Jahiliya in us.

00:48:17.670 --> 00:48:19.310
We still have ignorance in us

00:48:19.310 --> 00:48:21.150
whereby people don't have children.

00:48:21.150 --> 00:48:23.070
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant them.

00:48:23.070 --> 00:48:24.750
After some time they adopt

00:48:24.750 --> 00:48:27.190
and they get so upset if you say,

00:48:27.190 --> 00:48:28.870
is this your child?

00:48:28.870 --> 00:48:29.950
What do you mean, is this my child?

00:48:29.950 --> 00:48:31.990
This is my son, Allahu Akbar.

00:48:31.990 --> 00:48:33.790
But you sound like a man from Quraysh.

00:48:33.790 --> 00:48:35.390
Allah protect us.

00:48:35.390 --> 00:48:36.830
That's not supposed to be the case.

00:48:36.830 --> 00:48:37.910
Don't be embarrassed.

00:48:37.910 --> 00:48:39.790
Tell those children from a young age,

00:48:39.790 --> 00:48:41.550
we love you the most.

00:48:41.550 --> 00:48:43.950
We love you so much that we want to look after you.

00:48:43.950 --> 00:48:46.790
We will ensure that you have a good upbringing.

00:48:46.790 --> 00:48:49.070
We will be just as your parents,

00:48:49.070 --> 00:48:50.950
but your parents are someone else.

00:48:51.910 --> 00:48:53.030
This is Islam.

00:48:53.030 --> 00:48:54.710
We need to be honest and open

00:48:54.710 --> 00:48:55.870
and we need to make amends.

00:48:55.870 --> 00:48:57.190
There is nothing wrong.

00:48:57.190 --> 00:48:59.190
And every time we speak about this

00:48:59.190 --> 00:49:01.190
because of the Western system

00:49:01.190 --> 00:49:03.950
that sometimes we find ourselves drowning in,

00:49:03.950 --> 00:49:04.990
people are shocked.

00:49:04.990 --> 00:49:05.830
They say, what?

00:49:05.830 --> 00:49:06.990
We've never heard this before.

00:49:06.990 --> 00:49:08.870
But this is the deen from the beginning.

00:49:08.870 --> 00:49:11.030
It is known just like wudu and salah.

00:49:11.030 --> 00:49:12.070
This is the law.

00:49:12.070 --> 00:49:13.430
Anyone who wanted to know it,

00:49:13.430 --> 00:49:14.470
it's in the Quran.

00:49:14.470 --> 00:49:16.910
You can just open it and see Suratul Ahzab.

00:49:16.910 --> 00:49:18.070
Read what it says there.

00:49:18.070 --> 00:49:19.030
Allahu Akbar.

00:49:19.030 --> 00:49:20.190
Clear cut verses.

00:49:20.190 --> 00:49:21.750
Do not call someone your son

00:49:21.750 --> 00:49:23.510
when he is not your son, it's over.

00:49:23.510 --> 00:49:26.390
And the only time a person is to be called

00:49:26.390 --> 00:49:27.870
by the name of the mother

00:49:27.870 --> 00:49:29.990
is when that child is illegitimate

00:49:29.990 --> 00:49:31.950
or the father is unknown.

00:49:31.950 --> 00:49:33.030
Allah protect us.

00:49:33.030 --> 00:49:36.110
If you find in the whole book,

00:49:36.110 --> 00:49:39.030
in all the scriptures from the beginning right to the end,

00:49:39.030 --> 00:49:43.270
the only person who is called the son of a mother

00:49:43.270 --> 00:49:44.350
is Isa.

00:49:44.350 --> 00:49:46.390
وَإِذْ قَالَ عِيْسَ بَنُوا مَرْيَمْ

00:49:46.390 --> 00:49:47.710
Jesus, the son of Mary.

00:49:47.710 --> 00:49:48.550
Why?

00:49:48.550 --> 00:49:49.590
He did not have a father.

00:49:49.590 --> 00:49:51.470
It was Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:49:51.470 --> 00:49:54.070
who miraculously caused the birth of Jesus

00:49:54.070 --> 00:49:55.710
may peace be upon him.

00:49:55.710 --> 00:49:57.350
So that is why he is known as Jesus,

00:49:57.350 --> 00:49:58.230
the son of Mary.

00:49:58.230 --> 00:50:00.190
When it comes to anyone else,

00:50:00.190 --> 00:50:02.790
they are never referred to as son of so and so

00:50:02.790 --> 00:50:03.790
with the mother's name.

00:50:03.790 --> 00:50:05.670
Nowadays I know of cases where

00:50:05.670 --> 00:50:07.870
the mothers feel that you know we have equal rights

00:50:07.870 --> 00:50:10.910
so now you must put my name in the name as well.

00:50:10.910 --> 00:50:12.910
So they say so and so,

00:50:12.910 --> 00:50:14.550
son of the mother, son of the father.

00:50:14.550 --> 00:50:15.390
Allahu Akbar.

00:50:15.390 --> 00:50:17.430
You're not going to lose or gain anything by that.

00:50:17.430 --> 00:50:18.510
This is Allah's plan.

00:50:18.510 --> 00:50:21.270
Allah says you are called by your father.

00:50:21.270 --> 00:50:22.750
So it's nothing bad.

00:50:22.750 --> 00:50:25.590
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:50:25.590 --> 00:50:29.230
and may He open our doors and grant us acceptance.

00:50:29.230 --> 00:50:31.030
So Zayd ibn Haritha,

00:50:31.030 --> 00:50:32.110
radiallahu anhu,

00:50:32.110 --> 00:50:35.350
from that day nobody ever called him

00:50:35.350 --> 00:50:37.230
Zayd ibn Muhammad again.

00:50:37.230 --> 00:50:38.950
Everything that had happened,

00:50:38.950 --> 00:50:41.270
even when hadith was recorded,

00:50:41.270 --> 00:50:43.950
his name was recorded as Zayd ibn Haritha

00:50:43.950 --> 00:50:45.230
from the very beginning

00:50:45.230 --> 00:50:48.870
because they had recorded it after this verse was revealed.

00:50:48.870 --> 00:50:50.190
And for your information,

00:50:50.230 --> 00:50:52.990
the only companion of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:50:52.990 --> 00:50:55.590
whose name is in the Quran is Zayd,

00:50:55.590 --> 00:50:57.070
Zayd ibn Haritha.

00:50:57.070 --> 00:50:58.950
And this is in Surah Al-Ahzab.

00:50:58.950 --> 00:51:00.510
And this shows the love.

00:51:00.510 --> 00:51:02.790
No one must think the messenger didn't love him.

00:51:02.790 --> 00:51:03.950
Look, they changed the name.

00:51:03.950 --> 00:51:05.910
Allah loves him so much.

00:51:05.910 --> 00:51:08.950
He was known as Hibbu Rasulillah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:51:08.950 --> 00:51:12.110
the most beloved to the messenger sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:51:12.110 --> 00:51:13.630
that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:51:13.630 --> 00:51:16.270
chose to put his name in the Quran,

00:51:16.270 --> 00:51:18.310
yet the names of the other companions

00:51:18.310 --> 00:51:19.590
are not in the Quran.

00:51:19.590 --> 00:51:21.950
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to open our doors

00:51:21.950 --> 00:51:24.350
and grant us goodness tomorrow, inshallah.

00:51:24.350 --> 00:51:26.590
We will go straight into the events

00:51:26.590 --> 00:51:29.750
that led up to the treaty of Hudaibiyah

00:51:29.750 --> 00:51:32.710
and why exactly it happened and how exactly it happened.

00:51:32.710 --> 00:51:35.110
But before we get there, inshallah,

00:51:35.110 --> 00:51:36.910
and before we close this evening,

00:51:36.910 --> 00:51:40.430
I'd like to make mention that there were many skirmishes

00:51:40.430 --> 00:51:45.440
that took place after the Battle of the Trench.

00:51:45.440 --> 00:51:47.400
Why were there many skirmishes?

00:51:47.400 --> 00:51:49.360
Because there were so many parties

00:51:49.360 --> 00:51:52.760
that had taken part in that particular alliance

00:51:52.760 --> 00:51:55.120
that the Muslims had scores to settle.

00:51:55.120 --> 00:51:56.480
They had to go to those people

00:51:56.480 --> 00:51:58.160
who had engaged in a crime before.

00:51:58.160 --> 00:52:00.560
Those people, the people of Raji'

00:52:00.560 --> 00:52:03.800
who had slaughtered the 10 companions we spoke about

00:52:03.800 --> 00:52:04.640
and so on.

00:52:04.640 --> 00:52:07.080
So these battles had taken place.

00:52:07.080 --> 00:52:09.240
All of them, the Muslims were victorious.

00:52:09.240 --> 00:52:12.000
In fact, most of them, there was no actual battle.

00:52:12.000 --> 00:52:13.200
It was just a skirmish.

00:52:13.200 --> 00:52:15.760
When the Muslims had come, these people were frightened.

00:52:15.760 --> 00:52:17.960
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:52:18.000 --> 00:52:20.960
Insha'Allah, we will see how the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:52:20.960 --> 00:52:22.080
had a dream.

00:52:22.080 --> 00:52:25.960
And in his dream, he saw that he himself

00:52:25.960 --> 00:52:28.800
with his companions were entering Makkah

00:52:28.800 --> 00:52:30.520
whilst their heads were shaved

00:52:30.520 --> 00:52:33.400
and some of them, their hair was very cut, very short

00:52:33.400 --> 00:52:35.040
and they were going into Makkah

00:52:35.040 --> 00:52:38.840
and he knew that this means we should be going for Umrah

00:52:38.840 --> 00:52:41.040
and therefore he made an announcement

00:52:41.040 --> 00:52:44.840
amongst his companions, we will now proceed for Umrah.

00:52:44.840 --> 00:52:46.520
How were they going to go?

00:52:46.560 --> 00:52:48.520
Quraysh is waiting there with armies.

00:52:48.520 --> 00:52:50.240
The people around are all waiting

00:52:50.240 --> 00:52:52.040
with all their enmity and hatred.

00:52:52.040 --> 00:52:53.720
Tomorrow we will see what happened, insha'Allah,

00:52:53.720 --> 00:52:54.560
until then.

00:52:54.560 --> 00:52:56.880
Wa salallahu wa sallam wa baraka ala nabina Muhammad.

00:52:56.880 --> 00:52:58.040
Subhanallahi bi hamdi.

00:52:58.040 --> 00:53:00.960
Subhanaka Allahumma bi hamdika nashhadu alla ilaha illa anta.

00:53:00.960 --> 00:53:02.480
Nastaghfiruka wa natubu ilayk.

00:53:02.480 --> 00:53:06.320
Alhamdu lillahi Rabbil alameen

00:53:06.320 --> 00:53:08.960
Ar-Rahman Ar-Raheem

00:53:08.960 --> 00:53:12.000
Maaliki yawm al deen

00:53:12.000 --> 00:53:13.560
Iyyaka na'bubin
